{{EngvarB|date=September 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=September 2014}} [[File:Tun Abdul Ghaffar Baba Memorial.png|thumb|Tun Abdul Ghafar Baba Memorial]]
The '''Tun Abdul Ghafar Baba Memorial''' ({{lang-ms|Memorial Tun Abdul Ghafar Baba}}) is a museum in [[Peringgit]], [[Melaka]], [[Malaysia]]. The museum commemorates the life of former [[Deputy Prime Minister of Malaysia]], [[Ghafar Baba|Tun Ghafar Baba]].<ref>http://www.arkib.gov.my/web/guest/memorial-tun-abdul-ghafar-baba</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bernama.com/bernama/state_news/bm/news.php?id=323865&cat=ut|title=Berita Wilayah|work=bernama.com}}</ref>
==History== The building was constructed in 1956. The building used to be Ghafar Baba's residence when he was the [[List of Chief Ministers of Malacca|Chief Minister of Malacca]] in 1959-1967. In 2006, the building was converted into a museum and was opened to the public.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://amazingmelaka.com/2011/12/tun-abdul-ghafar-babas-memorial/|title=Tun Abdul Ghafar Baba’s Memorial|work=AmazingMelaka.com}}</ref>
==Exhibitions== The memorial is divided into two exhibition halls. The lower hall displays most of his personal belongings during his reign as Chief Minister of Malacca, Minister and Deputy Prime Minister. The upper hall displays his various souvenirs, photos, books, television set, furniture and fittings that were used by him and his family.
==Opening time== The memorial is open from Tuesday to Sunday from 9.00 a.m. to 6.00 p.m. free of charge.
